          <p style="margin: 15px; font-size: larger;">
      Personal Loans:

Purpose: Personal loans are unsecured loans that can be used for any personal expenses or financial needs.
Features and Benefits: Personal loans typically have a fixed interest rate and a fixed repayment period. They can be used for debt consolidation, home improvements, medical expenses, vacations, or other personal purposes.
Reason: Personal loans are suitable for individuals who need funds for personal expenses but may not have collateral to secure the loan.


      </p>
      <br>

     <p style="margin: 15px; font-size: larger;">
Mortgage Loans:

Purpose: Mortgage loans, also known as home loans, are used to finance the purchase of a property or real estate.
Features and Benefits: Mortgage loans have longer repayment periods (usually 15 to 30 years) and may have fixed or adjustable interest rates. The property being purchased acts as collateral for the loan.
Reason: Mortgage loans are suitable for individuals or families looking to buy a home or invest in real estate.
      </p>
<br>
    <p style="margin: 15px; font-size: larger;">

Auto Loans:

Purpose: Auto loans are specifically designed to finance the purchase of a vehicle, such as a car, motorcycle, or truck.
Features and Benefits: Auto loans have fixed interest rates and repayment terms. The vehicle being purchased serves as collateral for the loan, and the ownership transfers to the borrower upon full repayment.
Reason: Auto loans are ideal for individuals who want to purchase a vehicle but may not have the full amount upfront.

      </p>
      <br>
      <p  style="margin: 15px; font-size: larger;">
Student Loans:

Purpose: Student loans are intended to help students finance their education expenses, including tuition fees, books, and living costs.
Features and Benefits: Student loans may have flexible repayment options, including deferred payment until after graduation. Interest rates can be fixed or variable, depending on the loan type and terms.
Reason: Student loans are suitable for students pursuing higher education who need financial assistance to cover the costs of their studies.
      </p>
<br>

           <p  style="margin: 15px; font-size: larger;">
        Business Loans:

Purpose: Business loans are provided to entrepreneurs and businesses to support their operations, expansion, or specific business needs.
Features and Benefits: Business loans can be secured or unsecured, depending on the loan amount and terms. They can help businesses manage cash flow, purchase equipment, finance inventory, or fund growth initiatives.
Reason: Business loans are suitable for small businesses, startups, or established companies that require additional capital for their operations or growth plans.
</p>

